AS INTRODUCED
6
7
An Act relating to real estate brokers; amending 59
7
O.S. 2021, Section 858-355.1, which relates to
8
brokerage agreements; prohibiting requirement to
8
enter into certain agreement prior to certain
9
actions; prohibiting requirement for broker to enter
9
into certain agreement to show certain real estate;
10
allowing certain brokers to require certain associate
10
to enter into certain agreement prior to certain
11
action; providing for codification; and providing an
11
effective date.
12
12
13
13
14
BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
14
15
SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 59 O.S. 2021, Section 858-355.1,
15
16
is amended to read as follows:
16
17
Section 858-355.1. A. All brokerage agreements shall
17
18
incorporate as material terms the duties and responsibilities set
18
19
forth in Section 858-353 of The Oklahoma Real Estate License Code.
19
20
B. A broker may provide brokerage services to one or both
20
21
parties in a transaction.
21
22
C. A broker who is providing brokerage services to one or both
22
23
parties shall describe and disclose in writing the broker’s duties
23
24
and responsibilities set forth in Section 858-353 of The Oklahoma
24
Req. No. 2229 Page 1

1
Real Estate License Code prior to the party or parties signing a
1
2
contract to sell, purchase, lease, option, or exchange real estate.
2
3
D. A firm that provides brokerage services to both parties in a
3
4
transaction shall provide written notice to both parties that the
4
5
firm is providing brokerage services to both parties to a
5
6
transaction prior to the parties signing a contract to purchase,
6
7
lease, option, or exchange real estate.
7
8
E. If a broker intends to provide fewer brokerage services than
8
9
those required to complete a transaction, the broker shall provide
9
10
written disclosure to the party for whom the broker is providing
10
11
brokerage services. Such disclosure shall include a description of
11
12
those steps in the transaction for which the broker will not provide
12
13
brokerage services, and also state that the broker assisting the
13
14
other party in the transaction is not required to provide assistance
14
15
with these steps in any manner.
15
16
F. A broker shall not be required to enter into a written
16
17
brokerage agreement prior to showing a property for purchase, lease,
17
18
option, or exchange.
18
19
SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
19
20
in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 858-355.2 of Title 59, unless
20
21
there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
21
22
A. A broker shall not be required to enter into a brokerage
22
23
agreement with a buyer prior to showing real estate for purchase,
23
24
lease, option, or exchange.
24
Req. No. 2229 Page 2

1
B. A managing broker or proprietor broker may choose to require
1
2
a branch broker, broker associate, or sales associate that is
2
3
employed by, working with, or an independent contractor for the
3
4
managing broker or proprietor broker to enter into a brokerage
4
5
agreement with a buyer prior to showing real estate for purchase,
5
6
lease, option, or exchange.
6
7
SECTION 3. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
